				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shaggydredlocks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1722371); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1722371&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225791" alt="Shaggydredlocks" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1722371)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shaggydredlocks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1722371); return false;" >Shaggydredlocks</a></span> <span class="odate time_1484799058 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Jan 2017 04:10</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2729471">
									

<p>This is definitely fits the focus of several other SCP 001's (an SCPF origin) and while I feel it lacks some of the disquieting grandeur of proposals such as the Guardian and the Broken God, it more than makes up for it with the depth of the alternate/'actual' history, as well as the division of the O5's over how to proceed.</p>
<p>The rewriting of the file number itself is really humbling, and that instills a feeling of finality and catharsis I have not felt with other proposals. I do think that 'Wrong Proposal' reinforces that theme, and prefer the title sans apostrophe.</p>
<p>Certainly fitting for the spot. +1.</p>

							</div>

								
					
