					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1372582&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225791" alt="Jacob Conwell" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1372582)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jacob-conwell" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1372582); return false;" >Jacob Conwell</a></span> <span class="odate time_1484814084 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Jan 2017 08:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2729531">
									

<p>Oh hey! This got posted! Sweet!</p>
<p>While there is no shortage of alternative history during this, the 2017 History Contest, I have to admire how full force this skip goes into constructing that alternate history. Where as other skips kind of tack alternate timelines on as an addition to a different effect, the effect here is the alternate timeline, which is pretty neat.</p>
<p>On top of that, you do a good job making the original 13 O5 members have distinct personalities and characters matching with their original organizations. Thats quite a feat, in my opinion, given the small excerpts we see from them, via their letters to their replacements.</p>
<p>Overall, this is both a fun addition to HisCon17 and a fun 001 proposal.</p>
<p>+1 MrWrong</p>

							</div>

								
					
