<blockquote>
<p>On top of that, you do a good job making the original 13 O5 members have distinct personalities and characters matching with their original organizations. Thats quite a feat, in my opinion, given the small excerpts we see from them, via their letters to their replacements.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Indeed. That was one of the most difficult aspects when writing this (how to showcase thirteen different people). I must thank Petrograd since he gave a strong critique on the various notes, and made me change O5-3 and O5-10's notes entirely to the versions we now see. Also, it was my PM with fuban that gave me the idea that not all precursors have to be supported by their governments or at their prime (leading to O5-10's letter).</p>

